{{Infobox language |name=Kenga |nativename= |states=[[Chad]] |region= |speakers=40,000 |date=1997 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic]] |fam3=[[Bongo–Bagirmi languages|Bongo–Bagirmi]] |fam4=[[Bagirmi languages|Bagirmi]] |iso3=kyq |glotto=keng1240 |glottorefname=Kenga }}
'''Kenga''' is a [[Bongo–Bagirmi languages|Bongo–Bagirmi language]] of [[Chad]].
==References== {{Reflist}}
{{Central Sudanic languages}} [[Category:Languages of Chad]] [[Category:Bongo-Bagirmi languages]]
{{ns-lang-stub}}

In mathematics, the '''Kneser–Tits problem''', introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Tits|authorlink=Jacques Tits|year=1964}} based on a suggestion by [[Martin Kneser]], asks whether the Whitehead group ''W''(''G'',''K'') of a semisimple  simply connected isotropic [[algebraic group]] ''G'' over a [[field (mathematics)|field]] ''K'' is trivial. The Whitehead group is the quotient of the [[rational point]]s of ''G'' by the [[normal subgroup]] generated by ''K''-subgroups isomorphic to the additive group.

==Fields for which the Whitehead group vanishes==

A special case of the Kneser–Tits problem asks for which fields the Whitehead group of a semisimple almost simple  simply connected [[linear algebraic group|isotropic algebraic group]] is always trivial.
{{harvtxt|Platonov|1969}} showed that this Whitehead group is trivial for  [[local field]]s ''K'', and gave examples of fields for which it is not always trivial. For global fields the combined work of several authors shows that this Whitehead group is always trivial {{harv|Gille|2009}}.

==References==

*{{Citation | last1=Gille | first1=Philippe | title=Le problème de Kneser-Tits | url=http://www.dma.ens.fr/~gille/prepublis/bbki.pdf | series=Séminaire Bourbaki exp. 983 | isbn=978-2-85629-269-3 | mr=2605318  | year=2009 | journal=Astérisque | issn=0303-1179 | issue=326 | pages= 39–81 }}
*{{Citation | last1=Platonov | first1=V. P. | title=The problem of strong approximation and the Kneser–Tits hypothesis for algebraic groups | mr=0258839  | year=1969 | journal=Izvestiya Akademii Nauk SSSR. Seriya Matematicheskaya | issn=0373-2436 | volume=33 | pages=1211–1219}}
*{{Citation | last1=Tits | first1=Jacques | title=Séminaire Bourbaki, 29e année (1976/77) | url=http://www.numdam.org/item?id=SB_1976-1977__19__218_0 | publisher=[[Springer-Verlag]] | location=Berlin, New York | series=Lecture Notes in Math. | mr=521771  | year=1978 | volume=677 | chapter=Groupes de Whitehead de groupes algébriques simples sur un corps (d'après V. P. Platonov et al.) | pages=218–236}}
