{{dictionary}}
'''Septate''' is a [[morphology (biology)|morphological]] term defined in biology in two different instances:

*In human biology, it is used to describe a divide. For example, a septate uterus would be a divided uterus.
*In [[mycology]], it is used to describe the condition of [[spore]]s or [[hyphae]] that possess or lack a [[septum|septa]] to divide cells.

