{{Infobox language family |name=Talamanca |region=Costa Rica, Panama |familycolor=American |fam1 = [[Chibchan]] |glotto=none |glotto2=west2641 |glottoname2=partial match |glottorefname2=Western Isthmic Chibchan }}
The '''Talamanca languages''' are a well-defined{{dubious|date=April 2014}} branch of [[Chibchan languages]] spoken in central–southern Costa Rica and northern Panama. They are: :[[Huetar language|Huetar]] (Güetar), [[Bribri language|Bribri]] (Talamanca), [[Cabécar language|Cabécar]] (Talamanca), [[Chánguena language|Chánguena]], [[Teribe language|Teribe]] (Quequexque, Naso), and maybe [[Movere language|Movere]] (Move).{{fix|text=Is this supposed to be Guaymi?}}
